# SocratiCode-specific ignores (gitignore syntax).
#
# Exclude git worktrees from indexing and the dependency graph. Each worktree
# under .claude/worktrees/ is a full copy of the repo, so without this rule the
# graph balloons ~17x (one node per copy) and fragments — `codebase_impact` /
# graph queries on a real file return nothing because data is split across
# per-worktree path namespaces.
#
# Note: the global core.excludesFile (~/.config/git/ignore) that hides these from
# `git` is NOT read by SocratiCode — only repo-root/nested .gitignore and this
# file are. So the rule must live here even though git already ignores it.
#
# Scope: only the per-worktree copies are dropped. The canonical design-mocks/
# at the repo root stays fully indexed.
.claude/worktrees/
